    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presented is an investment-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, a masterclass in longitudinal front-midship engineering. This specimen retains its original 13B-REW rotary powerplant, featuring a flawlessly calibrated sequential twin-turbocharger system that ensures a seamless transition and linear power delivery through the rev range. The chassis maintains its factory-spec 50/50 weight distribution, supported by an uncompromised double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential. To ensure long-term thermal reliability, the cooling stack has been professionally refreshed while maintaining an OEM-plus aesthetic. The interior plastics and high-wear surfaces show zero UV degradation or typical fatigue. This is a rare, unmodified example with a documented service history, emphasizing mechanical integrity and peak kinematic performance.",
